## Examples

Example friction_type:
{"type_name": "kept-fixing-wrong-thing", "description": "You said the test setup was wrong, but the agent kept changing the check instead.", "severity": 4, "example_refs": [...]}

Example mitigation (note: `title` speaks to the user, `action` speaks to the agent):
{"title": "Check Test Setup Before Editing Assertions", "action": "Before modifying a failing test's assertions, read the test's setup and fixtures first. If setup looks wrong, fix setup, not the assertion.", "rationale": "The agent repeatedly edited assertions when the real problem was setup.\n- Reading setup first reveals the real cause\n- Prevents the repeat-edit cycle", "confidence": 0.85, "addressed_friction_types": ["kept-fixing-wrong-thing"]}

